This paper discusses the use of social networks to spread misinformation and fake news, which falls under the category of social media analysis and cybercrime. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Other possible sub-categories include cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.SD (Software Engineering), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
